    "title": "Indicate network in the Node window title - similar to the main window",
    "body": "While testing/reviewing PR https://github.com/bitcoin-core/gui/pull/414\r\n\r\nI was running Bitcoin-Qt.app concurrently with different active networks.\r\nI noticed that it may be useful to indicate the network in the Node window title - similar to the main window title.\r\nAdditionally you can see that the task bar ornaments are crowded when the main window is minimized.\r\nWhen the proxy setting is enabled - the \"P\" adds to the crowding.\r\n\r\nNOTE: it may be useful to modify the global styling template based on network selected.\r\nAdding an appropriate background color tint to the gui may be a good fix as well as the title modification.\r\n\r\n ![Screen Shot 2022-02-08 at 1 00 02 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/152159/153055744-363f1f0c-730c-4992-a7b6-5bc450d23897.png)\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-02-08 at 1 47 58 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/152159/153055766-aee12444-029d-4e72-9eeb-0a7725065458.png)\r\n\r\n",
